Well, the thing about Surveying is first you get the degree, THEN you have to do two years supervised work, and only THEN are you handed your badge as a chartered surveyor.
Its similar to going into Architectural Engineering. First get the bachelor's degree and take the FE exam, then after four years of supervised work take the PE exam in order to become certified.

Only thing kinda like that in VO is getting into SAG AFTRA. To apply for a position in SAG, you have to take part in several SAG productions. To take part in a SAG production, you have to be a member of SAG. It's literally the most catch-22 thing ever.
The only way in essentially is to know somebody who knows somebody who can get your name on a list.
